The paper presents a decentralized collision avoidance algorithm for navigating a swarm of quadrotors in dense environments, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The algorithm utilizes Model Predictive Control (MPC) and Kalman filtering, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.AI) and control theory (cs.MA). The paper also evaluates the performance of the algorithm with other state-of-the-art methods, which involves statistical analysis (cs.LG).
